<refentry xml:id="vtiful-kernel-excel.defineName" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">
 <refnamediv>
  <refname>Vtiful\Kernel\Excel::defineName</refname>
  <refpurpose>Vtiful\Kernel\Excel defineName</refpurpose>
 </refnamediv>
 <refsect1 role="description">
  &reftitle.description;
  <methodsynopsis>
   <modifier>public</modifier> <type>Vtiful\Kernel\Excel</type> <methodname>Vtiful\Kernel\Excel::defineName</methodname>
   <methodparam><type>string</type><parameter>name</parameter></methodparam>
   <methodparam><type>string</type><parameter>formula</parameter></methodparam>
   <methodparam choice="opt"><type class="union"><type>string</type><type>null</type></type><parameter>scopeSheet</parameter></methodparam>
  </methodsynopsis>
  <simpara>Creates a defined name in the workbook, which can be used as a named range or as a constant in formulas.</simpara>
 </refsect1>
 <refsect1 role="parameters">
  &reftitle.parameters;
  <variablelist>
   <varlistentry>
    <term><parameter>name</parameter></term>
    <listitem>
     <simpara>The name to define.</simpara>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <term><parameter>formula</parameter></term>
    <listitem>
     <simpara>The formula or cell range the name refers to.</simpara>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <term><parameter>scopeSheet</parameter></term>
    <listitem>
     <simpara>When provided, the name is scoped to the given worksheet and registered as <literal>Sheet!Name</literal>. When &null;, the name has workbook scope.</simpara>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
 </refsect1>
 <refsect1 role="returnvalues">
  &reftitle.returnvalues;
  <simpara>Returns the current <classname>Vtiful\Kernel\Excel</classname> instance, allowing method chaining.</simpara>
 </refsect1>
</refentry>
